handist.collections.dist

Class DistMap<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • handist.collections.dist.DistMap<K,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - type of the key used in the DistMap
    V - type of the value mapped to each key in the DistMap
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    apgas.util.SerializableWithReplace, DistributedCollection<V,DistMap<K,V>>, KeyRelocatable<K>, Serializable, Map<K,V>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DistIdMap, DistMultiMap

    public class DistMap<K,V>
extends Object
implements Map<K,V>, DistributedCollection<V,DistMap<K,V>>, KeyRelocatable<K>, apgas.util.SerializableWithReplace
    A Map data structure spread over the multiple places.

      • setProxyGenerator

        public void setProxyGenerator(Function<K,V> proxy)
        Sets the proxy generator for this instance.

        The proxy will be used to generate values when accesses to a key not contained in this instance is made. Instead of throwing an exception, the proxy will be called with the attempted index and the program will continue with the value returned by the proxy.

        This feature is similar to Map.getOrDefault(Object, Object) operation, the difference being that instead of returning a predetermined default value, the provided function is called with the key.

        Parameters:
        proxy - function which takes a key "K" as parameter and returns a "V", or null to remove any previously set proxy

      • writeReplace

        public Object writeReplace()
                    throws ObjectStreamException
        Description copied from interface: DistributedCollection
        Method used to create an object which will be transferred to a remote place.

        This method is present in interface DistributedCollection to force the implementation in implementing classes. Implementation should return a LazyObjectReference instance capable of initializing the local handle of the implementing class on the remote place

        Specified by:
